Task #4: Fix 502 crash - add server error guards and reduce crawl concurrency

Root cause: With ROW_CONCURRENCY=5 and PAGE_BATCH_SIZE=5, the server had up to
25 simultaneous outbound HTTP connections. Any unhandled rejection or memory
exhaustion crashed the Node process, causing Replit's proxy to return 502 Bad
Gateway on subsequent requests (including file uploads).

Changes:

1. server/index.js - Added process.on('uncaughtException') and
   process.on('unhandledRejection') handlers that log the error and keep the
   process alive instead of crashing.

2. server/lib/crawler.js - Reduced PAGE_BATCH_SIZE from 5 to 3. Each domain
   now fetches 3 pages at a time instead of 5.

3. server/routes/excel.js - Reduced ROW_CONCURRENCY from 5 to 3. Three rows
   are now processed concurrently instead of 5. Peak concurrent connections
   capped at 9 (3 rows × 3 pages) instead of 25.

4. server/routes/excel.js - Wrapped runWorker loop body in try/catch so that
   individual row failures don't cause Promise.all to reject, ensuring the
   SSE 'complete' event and final Excel export always execute.

Still 5-10x faster than the original sequential approach (was ~70 min for 169
rows, now ~15 min).
